cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for multi-task learning using a generalized tensor trace norm. It also involves experiments on real-world datasets to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as multi-task learning is a common technique in these fields. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be possible categories as they involve learning from large datasets and the use of deep learning techniques.
